data.meta_description: U.S. Congressman. He graduated from Valparaiso College, Indiana, in 1886 and taught school in Dallas County, Texas. Moving to Colorado, he taught school in Gilpin County (1887-88), was school principal in Black Hawk (1888-89) and was superintendent of public schools at Idaho Springs (1890-99).
